candidate_text: What a unique idea!

(Verse 1)
In the dead of night, I'm up and awake,
The washer's hummin', it's time to partake,
In this clandestine chore, where shadows play,
I sort the lights from the darks, by feelin' my way.

(Verse 1)
I'm sorting clothes in the dead of night,
The washing machine's hum, my only light.

(Verse 1)
I stumbled into the room, half asleep and alone 
The washing machine was calling, I had to atone 
For all the dirty clothes that piled up high 
But as I reached for the switch, I realized I'd said goodbye 

To the lights, it seemed they'd gone astray 
Now I'm sorting socks by feel, in a dark of day 
Whites from colors, delicates too 
It's a guessing game, but I'll see this through 

(Chorus) Doing laundry in the dark 
A midnight chore, without a spark 
Rinse and spin, in the darkness reigns 
Hoping I don't make any stains 

(Verse 2) Shirts and pants and sheets galore 
I match them up, or so I explore 
My hands move slow, my senses high 
As I fold and put away, before I say goodbye 

The rumble of the dryer's my guide 
A soothing sound, that's hard to hide 
As I work through the night 
Doing laundry, with no light 

(Chorus) Doing laundry in the dark 
A midnight chore, without a spark 
Rinse and spin, in the darkness reigns 
Hoping I don't make any stains 

(Bridge) It may not be easy, but I won't give in 
The darkness might just become my friend 
In the shadows, I find a peaceful place 
Where the laundry's done, without a single face 

(Chorus) Doing laundry in the dark 
A midnight chore, without a spark 
Rinse and spin, in the darkness reigns 
Hoping I don't make any stains 

(Outro) Now the cycle ends, and dawn begins 
The lights come on, and my task wins 
Fresh clean clothes, and a sense of pride 
Done in the dark, where love resided.
What an interesting prompt!
